description.value: Fragments of papyrus roll  inscribed in Demotic. = P. Leconte 9. Three pages, bounded by horizontal and vertical borders, parts of a hymn to Sobek, mentioning deities worshipped at Sobknopaiou Nesos (Isis Nephremnis, Isis Neferses, Sobeknopaios etc). Several hieratic signs in the text suggest it was copied from a hieratic original. Notable is the writing of demotic in columns (instead of lines) around the invocation of gods. The handwriting suggests that it  comes from Soknopaiou Nesos, early Roman period (Quack, pers. comm.).

Thompson's MS Catalogue: "mounted in ten frames. [...] The roll has lost its beginning (there are vestiges of a column preceding the first) and its end. It is all written in one hand. Contents. The first eight frames containing 26 columns consist of a collection of proverbs & moral sayings. Frames IX+X containing 4 columns and 9 fragments consist of portions of a historical romance, in which one Anch-Sheshanqy son of Djainofre(?) (cf. Spiegelberg, Petubastis Sage. p. 79 no. 31) seems to play a principal part."
